Panjiva Data Removal Guide
==========================

Overview
--------
Panjiva is a major trade intelligence platform that aggregates shipping and customs data. This guide covers removal procedures and best practices.

Understanding Panjiva
----------------------
- Operates under S&P Global Market Intelligence
- Sources data from customs agencies and shipping records
- Provides company profiles, trade relationships, and market analysis
- Used extensively by competitors for market research

Removal Process
---------------

Step 1: Identify Your Data
- Search for your company name and variants
- Check subsidiary and division names
- Look for supplier/customer relationships
- Note specific records and URLs

Step 2: Prepare Your Request
- Gather evidence of unwanted exposure
- Document business impact
- Prepare legal entity verification
- Reference privacy regulations where applicable

Step 3: Submit Removal Request
- Contact: privacy@panjiva.com
- Include: Company name, specific URLs, legal basis
- Reference: Data protection concerns and business impact
- Follow up: Track request status and response times

Step 4: Monitor and Follow Up
- Check removal completion
- Watch for reindexing or new data
- Document the process for future reference
- Set up monitoring for new exposures

Key Points
----------
- Panjiva may require verification of authority to request removal
- Some data may be considered public record and non-removable
- Removal timelines vary (typically 2-4 weeks)
- Data may reappear if new trade activity occurs

Alternative Approaches
----------------------
- Manifest confidentiality filing (proactive protection)
- Data suppression rather than complete removal
- Limiting specific fields rather than entire records
- Coordinated approach across related entities

Common Challenges
-----------------
- Verification of requestor authority
- Distinguishing between public record and aggregated data
- Handling of subsidiary and related entity data
- Managing ongoing trade activity

Template Request Language
-------------------------
"We request removal of [Company Name] data from Panjiva records due to [specific business concerns]. We have legitimate business interests in protecting our supplier relationships and trade patterns. Please confirm removal and provide timeline for completion."

This guide provides general procedures. For specific cases or complex situations, consider professional assistance from Remova.org or legal counsel.

